article.headline: S. Dakota St. 74, IPFW 43
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Chad White scored 15 points off the bench and South Dakota State was in control most of the way in a 74-43 victory over IPFW on Saturday night. Nate Wolters had 14 points and five assists for South Dakota State (17-6, 9-2 Summit). IPFW (10-11, 4-8) got 12 points from Mario Hines and 10 from Frank Gaines. White hit 4 of 5 shots from 3-point range, helping South Dakota State to a 9-of-20 effort. IPFW, meanwhile, was ice-cold from beyond the arc, making just 2 of 17 shots. IPFW led by a point with 13:06 left in the first half, but South Dakota State went on a 14-2 run for an 11-point lead with 7:51 left in the first half.
